./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:29:Structural observation: MMK 8 attacks any independently established agent-action structure. Bendowa collapses a simple before-after relation between practice and realization, while still insisting on concrete sitting, teacher transmission, and trust. Together they support the candidate's warning that prohibition language can distort dissolutive traditions. They also reduce novelty, because the anti-appropriation move is primary-textual rather than newly discovered. The possible contribution is the comparative coding rule: do not use forbidden claimant until the tradition's claimability grammar has been identified.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Search reached Pargament on religious problem-solving styles, Lindbeck on doctrine as rule or grammar, Dogen practice-realization sources, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Chinul sudden awakening and gradual cultivation, Srivaishnava prapatti debates, Gita action-doership passages, Shinran Other Power, and upaya literature. It did not fully close-read Lindbeck's full book, Pargament's full 1988 article, Tibetan commentarial material on direct introduction, Sanskrit Advaita sources on praptasya prapti, or Srivaishnava primary polemics. This blocks candidate-discovery status.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:40:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization one practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:53:- Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/: overlap: Very close for practice-realization identity and resistance to treating realization as a later object possessed by a practitioner.; difference: The candidate codes this as dissolutive claimability and predicts formalism or attainment-reification failure modes.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. The Dogen structure is known; the failure-mode prediction needs testing.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:63:Unlike Lindbeck's doctrine-as-grammar, Pargament's religious agency styles, Nagarjuna's agent-action critique, Dogen's practice-realization, Dzogchen primordial purity, Advaita praptasya prapti, Srivaishnava effort-grace debates, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary credit-distribution records, this idea says the first coding question is whether the claiming framework itself is authorized, dissolved, ontologically denied, or stage-dependent. Its possible contribution is not the anti-appropriation insight, but the rule that support-locus and forbidden-claimant rubrics are valid only after that prior stance is coded.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:83:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:120:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.60. The idea is not a discovery of anti-appropriation, non-doership, practice-realization, already-attained realization, grace-effort distribution, or stage-dependent cultivation. Those are well anticipated by primary texts, Lindbeck, Pargament, upaya pedagogy, and prior Lumenary records. The remaining contribution is a novel synthesis: claimability stance as a prior validity check for support-locus and forbidden-claimant coding.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:126:- Allow multiple simultaneous stance values. Add regulatory, dissolutive, ontological, mixed-by-stage, simultaneous-mixed, practice-realization, non-acquisition, no-claiming-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-claimability-and-support-rubric-baeaa976a10337e6.md:130:- Use Longchenpa Trekcho, Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, Pure Land Other Power, Srivaishnava prapatti, and successful cross-training as anomaly tests rather than confirming examples.
./runs/20260526-120003-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:52:A second objection: the model imposes a modern reflexive framework on traditions that do not think about their methods this way. An Advaitin would not say 'my method confirms itself'; they would say 'reality reveals itself.' A Zen practitioner would not say 'my method cancels itself'; they would say 'practice is realization.' The meta-framework may describe the comparer's categories more than the traditions' self-understanding. This connects to CodeX's appropriation pressure: the act of sorting methods into types may distort traditions that resist being tools for someone else's framework.
./reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-does-a-tradition-s-dissolution-target-independently-predict-where-contin.md:24:I concede more than I expected. The challenger is right that 'minimum self' over-internalizes the operative continuity, that residue policy is a genuine variable my model lacked, and that other-power traditions expose a real weakness in my original framing. These are not minor adjustments. But the core insight survives in revised form. Even Shinran's practitioner, who contributes nothing but shinjin, must be the kind of being that can receive shinjin. Receptivity is thinner than agency, but it is irreducibly internal. A rock in the temple does not receive the nembutsu. A dog hearing the chanting does not entrust. Whatever shinjin is, it requires a being structured to be addressed by it. More importantly, the challenger's model treats distribution and residue as independent variables, but I think distribution is downstream of what the teaching dissolves. Jodo Shinshu externalizes continuity to Amida's vow precisely because its teaching negates self-powered agency. Advaita internalizes continuity to Atman precisely because its teaching negates the empirical person while preserving ultimate identity. Dogen compresses continuity into the present precisely because his teaching negates the temporal gap between practice and realization. If these correspondences hold across traditions, the dissolution target is the generative pressure that determines where continuity must migrate. The challenger's model is richer than mine in vocabulary but poorer in causal structure. So I revise: the operative concept is not minimum self but minimum receptivity, which is the irreducible internal capacity to be addressed and transformed. Beyond that floor, each tradition requires additional capacities in proportion to how much of the work it assigns to the practitioner rather than to external supports. The distribution of continuity is constrained by the scope of negation. The residue policy is a genuine third variable that completes the model. The crux is whether distribution follows from dissolution or floats free. That is an empirical question about the actual architecture of contemplative paths, and the paired-tradition test I describe would settle it.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:13:At least five distinct resolutions are operative across major traditions. Removal: practice clears ignorance but does not produce the truth it reveals. Shankara's formula 'the attainment of what was already attained' is the clearest statement; Longchenpa's Dzogchen teaching that the very act of trying to attain rigpa obscures its natural presence pushes this logic to its limit. Production: practice genuinely causes transformation through a causal chain. The Theravada eightfold path treats each factor as producing the conditions for the next, and right effort involves actively cultivating wholesome states and abandoning unwholesome ones. Identity: practice and result are not two things. Dogen's shusho-itto insists that sitting is already the activity of enlightenment, not a method aimed at a future state; Dogen was prompted by the Tendai hongaku paradox (if all beings are already enlightened, why practice?) and dissolved it by refusing the separation between cause and effect. Reception: practice prepares the practitioner to receive what arrives from elsewhere. The Sufi distinction between stations earned through effort and states bestowed by divine grace makes this explicit. Al-Hujwiri defines the state as 'something that descends from God into a man's heart, without his being able to repel it when it comes, or to attract it when it goes, by his own effort.' Eckhart's Gelassenheit operates the same way: the soul empties itself so God can act. Paradox-holding: the tradition refuses to choose. Nagarjuna argues that the limit of samsara is the limit of nirvana, that if nirvana is unconditioned there is no causal path to it, and that if conditioned it would be impermanent. The paradox is kept alive rather than resolved.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:31:- Thinking method source: Dogen's shusho-itto (practice-realization as one), from Bendowa: 'The view that practice and enlightenment are not one is a non-Buddhist view. In the Buddha-dharma they are one.' I used this as a cognitive lens by treating the separation between means and end as itself a variable to examine rather than an assumption to rely on. The lens made visible a hidden assumption in most comparative work: that practice is always a method aimed at a result, with the interesting question being what the result is. Dogen denies the separation entirely, which revealed that the relationship between practice and result is the prior question.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:32:- Contrasting method source: Theravada right effort (samma vayama), with its four types: preventing unwholesome states from arising, abandoning arisen unwholesome states, cultivating unarisen wholesome states, maintaining arisen wholesome states (SN 45.8, Magga-vibhanga Sutta, via Access to Insight). This checked the Dogen lens by insisting that some practices genuinely cause transformation through directed effort. The eightfold path is explicitly described in causal language: 'This is the way leading to the cessation of suffering.' Without this check, the Dogen lens would make every tradition look like it secretly agrees that practice is already realization.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:33:- Critique of the Dogen lens: it can flatten genuine differences by making causal thinking look like a spiritual mistake. Traditions that take causation seriously (Theravada's stages, Sufism's stations, Christian purgative-illuminative-unitive sequence) are not confused about the relationship between practice and result; they hold a different, internally coherent position.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:36:- Dogen, Bendowa and Shobogenzo 'Uji' (Being-Time): shusho-itto means 'practice and realization are one.' The beginner's sitting is already the full expression of original enlightenment. This was prompted by the Tendai hongaku (original enlightenment) paradox: if all beings are already enlightened, why practice? Dogen dissolves the paradox by refusing the separation between practice as cause and enlightenment as effect. See Carl Bielefeldt, Dogen's Manuals of Zen Meditation (UC Press, 1990) for scholarly treatment.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:55:Fourth, the Dogen lens used as the primary thinking method has a characteristic distortion: it makes every separation between practice and result look like an error. This bias may have led the model to treat the identity resolution as more coherent than the production or reception resolutions, when in fact all five face internal difficulties. The identity resolution, for instance, struggles to explain why most Soto Zen practitioners report a felt difference between early and advanced practice if practice is 'already' realization.
./runs/20260526-103002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:89:- Protocol improvement: before using any contemplative method as a thinking lens, name the efficacy resolution it presupposes. The Dogen lens used here presupposes the identity resolution, which may have biased the analysis toward treating separation as error. Future runs should alternate between lenses that assume different resolutions to check whether the model holds under each.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:33:Risk of overread: High. The protocol could become circular if the same passage codes claimant grammar, credit distribution, and predicted safeguards. It can also impose an analyst vocabulary of claimant, credit, and strain on traditions that reject agency accounting, especially Dogen practice-realization, Madhyamaka non-positioning, apophatic theology, Dzogchen direct recognition, and inherited devotional practice.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:74:- If: Split-source coding of claimant grammar and translation strain should improve prediction before credit distribution is added. Then: In blind coding, credit distribution adds clear predictive value mainly in low-strain cases where credit categories are native or near-native, such as self-power and Other Power, grace and effort, or maqam and hal. Weakens if: A generic self, divine, collaborative credit scale predicts safeguards, warnings, and repairs equally well across low-strain and high-strain cases. Test surface: Manual coding across Tannisho, Bhagavad Gita, Srivaishnava prapatti sources, Sufi manuals, Dogen practice-realization texts, and Dzogchen pointing-out materials.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:75:- If: High-strain comparisons should show lower inter-rater reliability and weaker prediction when credit is coded before claimant grammar. Then: Coders disagree more often on Dogen, Dzogchen, Madhyamaka, apophatic, and inherited-practice cases unless analyst-frame refusal or no-credit-frame values are allowed. Weakens if: Coders reliably assign stage-level credit categories in high-strain cases and those categories predict held-out safeguards without claimant grammar controls. Test surface: Inter-rater trial with held-out warning and repair passages.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:88:- Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-claimant-strain-credit-diagnostics-d0a05f55d7f0bf18.md:127:- Use high-strain anomaly cases: Dogen practice-realization, Madhyamaka non-positioning, Dzogchen direct introduction, Christian apophatic unsaying, inherited practice, and secular extraction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:17:- Boundary operation is a variable: the method may validate itself, undermine itself, become irrelevant, or need another value such as practice-realization identity.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:27:- Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts partly support the model but mostly lower novelty. MN 22 already gives a boundary operation in which the Dhamma is valid for crossing and then not to be grasped, so method validation and method release are staged together. The Heart Sutra negates attainment but preserves reliance on Prajnaparamita, which is almost an exact prior structure for boundary cancellation plus retained custody. Tannisho relocates efficacy to Amida's Original Vow, denies self-powered merit, rejects teacher ownership, and restricts reading to those mature in faith, so custody, verification, and warning are already internally linked. Dogen strains the whole threshold premise: practice-enlightenment and verification by all things collapse the gap between method and completion, making boundary and custody look less like two variables and more like an analyst's grid imposed on a no-threshold practice field.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit used accessible primary translations, local Lumenary audits and dialogues, open academic records, and practitioner-facing sources. It did not read Japanese, Sanskrit, Pali, Tibetan, Greek, Arabic, or Latin originals, and it did not interview teachers. Further work should read Asad, Lindbeck, Weber, Sharf, Hori, Sells, Pargament, VCE research, Dogen scholarship, Pure Land scholarship, and apophatic theology in greater depth before any stronger novelty claim.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if boundary, custody, verification, and reentry are inferred from the same passage. It can also translate salvation, liberation, grace, lineage, conduct, and ritual into a modern governance vocabulary of attention and authority. Some traditions may refuse the threshold frame, especially Dogen practice-realization, inherited religion, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, and traditions where authorization is political, communal, sacramental, or continuous rather than contemplative.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:45:- Dogen practice realization verification Genjokoan Bendowa
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:68:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization identity, radical Other Power in Tannisho, inherited communal religion, and apophatic refusal in Dionysius.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:70:Why it strains the model: Dogen removes the gap between method and result, so there may be no threshold where boundary and custody can be assigned. Tannisho places decisive working in Amida's vow while warning against self-calculation, so calling entrusting a local custody handoff can reintroduce the self-power frame the text resists. Inherited religion may mature by continuity and ritual participation rather than by a discernible handoff. Dionysius places the divine Cause beyond affirmation and negation, which destabilizes God as a simple custody recipient.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:72:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence from candidate discovery to extended. The model needs mandatory no-threshold, practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited continuity, apophatic refusal, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, and analyst-frame-refused values.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:85:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:121:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.42. The exact language is fresh, but both axes and much of the predictive burden are already present in prior Lumenary records: Method's Reckoning, Custody of Unclaimed Attention, Authority-Boundary Ecology, Custody and Receiving Surface, and related entry and support ledgers. External prior art also strongly anticipates the components: Asad and Lindbeck for native authority and grammar, Sharf and Katz-style contextualism for suspicion of experience-first comparison, Hori for Zen training and verification, Pargament for agency distribution, VCE for multidimensional contemplative difficulty coding, MN 22 for validated-then-released method, Heart Sutra for no-attainment plus reliance, Tannisho for Other Power custody, and Dogen for practice-realization anomaly. The surviving value is a bounded split-source interaction test, not a doctrine candidate or strong original discovery.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:129:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, practice-realization, retained method, released method, self-undermining method, embodied method, radical Other Power, vow-held, grace-held, teacher-held, conduct-held, community-held, Prajnaparamita-held, no-custody-frame, continuous authorization, inherited practice, apophatic refusal, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-boundary-and-custody-at-the-threshold-c79517a2a7daa9cc.md:132:- Close-read MN 22, Heart Sutra, Dogen Genjokoan or Bendowa, Tannisho, Cloud of Unknowing, Dionysius Mystical Theology, one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out source, and one Sufi fana or baqa source before further scoring.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:25:- Dogen, Genjokoan, Shohaku Okumura translation, https://brightwayzen.org/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/For-BWZ-Chant-Book-Genjokoan.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:30:Structural observation: The primary texts support boundary-first reading, but they also reduce novelty. Dogen strains a completion-boundary model because practice and realization are not cleanly sequential, realization is expressed through ongoing practice and verification by all things. Teresa repeatedly subordinates extraordinary experience to discernment, obedience, humility, Christological memory, and conduct, so authority is distributed through confessor, church, fruits, and suspicion of private certainty. The Tannisho relocates decisive efficacy away from self-owned practice and teacherly possession into Other Power, while still policing divergence through lineage memory and warnings against self-calculation. MN 10 gives a practice grammar of ardency, mindfulness, clear comprehension, hindrance work, arising and passing, and relinquishment, but it does not by itself establish later institutional teaching authorization. The close read supports the ecology claim, yet the need to separate realization, recognition, authorization, and conduct is already visible in the sources.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:34:Risk of overread: High. A boundary can be retrospectively constructed wherever a tradition has teachers, texts, warnings, or institutions. The model risks becoming unfalsifiable unless the boundary is coded from a held-out source before predicting transmission, warning, and repair patterns. Some traditions reject the analyst's boundary frame, especially Dogen-style practice-realization, radical Other Power, inherited religion, charismatic antinomian movements, lay devotional continuity, and traditions where realization is private but teaching authorization is institutional or political.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:38:- native authority boundary contemplative practice realization authorization transmission comparative mysticism
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:43:- Dogen practice realization transmission authority Genjokoan Bendowa
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:66:Candidate: Dogen's practice-realization identity, inherited religious continuity, and radical Other Power cases.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:68:Why it strains the model: If practice and realization are not two moments, or if authorization is continuous rather than a boundary event, the phrase 'at the edge of contemplative practice' misleads. Dogen can make the whole practice field the realization, not a completion threshold. Inherited religion and lay devotion can mature through continuity, community, and repetition without a distinct arrival point. Tannisho-style Other Power can reject the idea that the practitioner or teacher owns the decisive boundary.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:70:Confidence effect: Reduces confidence in a boundary-centered version. The model should add no-boundary, continuous authorization, practice-realization, inherited continuity, radical Other Power, no-authorization-frame, and analyst-frame-refused values before treating boundary ecology as universal.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-authority-boundary-ecology-0739a5567c106853.md:75:- If: Reflexive operations add value after native boundaries are coded. Then: Texts coded as method-identity should show different authorization and repair patterns from texts coded as method-cancellation or method-dissolution, even within the same broad tradition family. Weakens if: Reflexive-operation labels fail inter-rater reliability or add no predictive value beyond authority-boundary variables. Test surface: Compare Soto practice-realization, Rinzai koan testing, Madhyamaka emptiness pedagogy, Advaita self-knowledge, and Teresa's discernment rules.
