./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-forbidden-claimant-rubric-ccc236ff67de7a3f.md:72:- If: Adverse practice events should sometimes cluster around wrong-claimant failures. Then: Gift practice shows self-power anxiety or false surrender, direct-introduction practice shows reification of recognition, practice-realization shows achievement seeking or empty formalism, and effort practice shows pride or mechanical striving. Weakens if: Adverse reports are fully explained by trauma history, retreat intensity, sleep loss, psychiatric vulnerability, poor supervision, or social isolation, with no added value from claimant coding. Test surface: Re-coding VCE-style interviews and teacher case consultations for prior training, current method, claimant language, and failure type.
