./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:37:Risk of overread: High. The model risks treating texts, teacher norms, report vocabulary, actual phenomenology, and embodied habit as one process. It also risks making every difference count as grain and every doctrinal sentence count as residue policy. Traditions such as Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence may reject the developmental sequence or the analyst's residue vocabulary.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:73:Candidate: Successful dual-trained or hybrid practitioners who switch methods smoothly after clear instruction, plus traditions that refuse the analyst's developmental sequence, especially Soto practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Pure Land Other Power, inherited practice, and apophatic silence.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:75:Why it strains the model: If practitioners can move from vipassana to Advaita, from self-inquiry to noting, from non-attachment to devotion, or from devotional prayer to deconstructive practice without old attentional habits persisting, then grain may be current ecology and vocabulary rather than embodied residue. If Pure Land or grace-held practice keeps efficacy outside practitioner-owned capacity, residue may not become the practitioner's grain at all. If Soto practice-realization collapses means and fruit, early and mature mismatch may not separate cleanly.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-layered-direction-and-residue-to-grain-conversion-0d0b8fe11600872e.md:139:- Add mandatory anomaly values: no-threshold, practice-realization, direct recognition, radical Other Power, grace-held support, inherited practice, successful dual practice, no-residue report, secular extraction, psychiatric vulnerability, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./runs/20260526-093002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:182:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
