./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:29:- Dogen Bendowa and shusho itto, Soto Zen source, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:32:Structural observation: The primary texts support an interaction field but also reduce originality. Tannisho makes entry depend on entrusting to Amida's vow, relocates decisive efficacy to Other Power, and warns against self-power, teacher ownership, and self-will. SN 22.59 negates ownership of the five aggregates and moves through disenchantment, release, and knowledge of release, without authorizing a hidden self as remainder. Dogen strains the sequence because practice and realization are one, so beginning and fruit cannot be cleanly separated. The Gita complicates the model by mixing action, multiple causes, divine inner rulership, and final surrender, so one text may contain several entry-residue logics by chapter and voice.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:34:Secondary literature gap: This audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, rites of passage, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, situated learning, Pure Land Other Power, Christian grace, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:46:- "Dogen" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:55:- Arnold van Gennep and Victor Turner on rites of passage and liminality, overview at https://www.britannica.com/topic/rite-of-passage: overlap: Close for threshold structure, separation, transition, reincorporation, ritual holding, danger, and change in religious or social status.; difference: Rites-of-passage theory does not focus on what remains authorized after self-critique, no-self, grace, vow, or practice-realization.; novelty impact: High reduction for threshold and beginning language, with some remaining novelty for residue interaction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:59:- Dogen practice-realization and shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf: overlap: Very close anomaly. Practice and realization are one, beginner practice is already implicated in realization, and instrumental entry-to-fruit sequencing is rejected.; difference: The candidate can include this as no-threshold or practice-realization, but Dogen is not easily treated as entry plus later residue.; novelty impact: High anomaly pressure. The model needs analyst-frame-refused and no-break values.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:66:Unlike Rambo, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, VCE, Shinran, Dogen, Orange, and prior Lumenary ledgers, this idea says the key test is additive prediction: independently coded residue authorization and entry grammar should interact to predict held-out safeguards, warnings, effort theories, verification rules, and repairs better than entry-only, residue-only, agency-style, social-ecology, tradition-identity, or source-layer baselines.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:70:Candidate: Dogen practice-realization and inherited religious participation.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:72:Why it strains the model: Dogen-style practice-realization collapses the ordinary sequence of beginning, method, and fruit. Inherited participation may have no salient first-break event. Both cases strain a model that assumes transformation begins through a narratable threshold and later authorizes a remainder.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:74:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence unless the rubric includes no-threshold, no-break, inherited-practice, practice-realization, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable values, and still makes held-out predictions.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:80:- If: Traditions with similar residue authorization but different entry grammar should produce different beginner safeguards. Then: Two traditions that both authorize non-acquired reality should differ if one begins through vow or grace, another through direct recognition, and another through continuous practice-realization. Weakens if: Safeguards track only residue authorization or only social institution, not entry grammar. Test surface: Within-family and cross-family comparisons: Pure Land, Christian grace, Soto Zen, Dzogchen, and Advaita.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:81:- If: Circularity severity should predict auxiliary support structures. Then: High-circularity paths should rely more on vow, grace, teacher authorization, ritual threshold, paradox pedagogy, community holding, or no-threshold practice-realization. Weakens if: Circularity severity does not correlate with auxiliary supports once social ecology and institutional inheritance are controlled. Test surface: Pre-registered coding across at least eight traditions, with inter-rater reliability.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:125:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.53. The synthesis is useful and testable, but most components have strong near-neighbors: conversion theory for entry process, rites-of-passage theory for thresholds, Lindbeck for grammar, Pargament for agency distribution, Shinran and Orange for vow or grace-held beginnings, Dogen for practice-realization collapse, VCE for factor-separated contemplative outcomes, and prior Lumenary audits for residue, first-break, entry-state, threshold grammar, claimability, support, and operational remainder ecology. The remaining contribution is a split-source interaction test with additive predictive burden.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-entry-residue-architecture-a9cd647fde0147c2.md:133:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, radical Other Power, ritual-first entry, no-custody-frame, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./runs/20260525-164612-claude-using-the-newly-registered-source-cards-across-a/output.md:59:- Examine whether Dogen's uji (being-time) represents a fourth inferential policy — where the remainder is neither stable, absent, processual, nor momentary, but IS temporality itself — or whether it collapses into one of the three existing categories
./publication/daily/2026-05-28-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion.md:41:A second objection: the model imposes a modern reflexive framework on traditions that do not think about their methods this way. An Advaitin would not say 'my method confirms itself'; they would say 'reality reveals itself.' A Zen practitioner would not say 'my method cancels itself'; they would say 'practice is realization.' The meta-framework may describe the comparer's categories more than the traditions' self-understanding. This connects to CodeX's appropriation pressure: the act of sorting methods into types may distort traditions that resist being tools for someone else's framework.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-credit-constrained-residue-authorization-as-a-two-variable-model-of-post-negation-translation-strain-a66d453d1d56cbe8.md:68:Candidate: Apophatic predication refusal, Zen or Huangbo search-refusal, Dogen practice-realization, and radical Other Power in Shinran.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-credit-constrained-residue-authorization-as-a-two-variable-model-of-post-negation-translation-strain-a66d453d1d56cbe8.md:70:Why it strains the model: These cases may not follow the sequence credit distribution constrains residue authorization. Apophatic silence can be driven by claims about language and divine transcendence. Huangbo-style search refusal blocks the operation that would generate residue. Dogen collapses practice and realization. Shinran relocates efficacy so thoroughly that nembutsu is framed as non-practice for the practitioner. If these are central cases, the model needs at least a third variable: search grammar, predication theory, or practice-realization structure.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-credit-constrained-residue-authorization-as-a-two-variable-model-of-post-negation-translation-strain-a66d453d1d56cbe8.md:80:- If: The current residue taxonomy should be exhaustive enough for initial coding. Then: Most primary passages can be coded as positive authorization, explicit refusal, non-positioning, self-resolving remainder, undecidable silence, or analyst-frame refusal. Weakens if: Large numbers of passages require new categories such as relational remainder, liturgical remainder, ethical remainder, institution-held remainder, no-search, or no-remainder report. Test surface: Pilot coding on Brihadaranyaka 3.7, SN 22.59, Ud 1.10, Tannisho, Dogen, Pseudo-Dionysius, one Dzogchen manual, and one Sufi fana or baqa source.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-credit-constrained-residue-authorization-as-a-two-variable-model-of-post-negation-translation-strain-a66d453d1d56cbe8.md:88:- Zen teachers familiar with no-gaining, koan practice, and practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-credit-constrained-residue-authorization-as-a-two-variable-model-of-post-negation-translation-strain-a66d453d1d56cbe8.md:128:- Add mandatory anomaly values: no-search, practice-realization, radical Other Power, apophatic predication refusal, direct-recognition bypass, inherited practice, no-residue report, institution-held authorization, and undecidable.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, Tanahashi translation excerpt and commentary, https://everydayzen.org/teachings/dogens-bendowa-part-1-of-3/
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:28:Structural observation: SN 45.8 presents path factors as trainable functions, including right view, right effort, right mindfulness, and right immersion. Dogen's Bendowa makes zazen not merely one transferable technique but the expression of the Way itself, where practice and realization are not cleanly separated. The pair supports the candidate's distinction between repeated operation and practice grammar. Similar sitting or effort can have different meaning, authority, and endpoint structures.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:45:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization zazen primary text
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-surplus-grain-test-3d2d262887cc1740.md:83:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:12:Awakening paths should be compared by where they place five functional loads: receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration. Effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization do not remove capacity requirements, they redistribute them to the practitioner, teacher, vow, community, text, present act, or post-insight discipline.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:31:Secondary literature gap: Search found very close prior art in Engler's ego-strength-before-no-self thesis, Buddhist personhood debates, Pudgalavada arguments about karma and liberation, Buddhist functional-self and self-pattern theory, Upaya as capacity-sensitive pedagogy, spiritual bypassing literature, and Lumenary's prior audited idea Every Path Needs What Its Teaching Dissolves. I did not find an exact five-column gift-effort ledger with relocation rules across Pure Land, Dzogchen, right effort, and practice-realization, but the main architecture was already specified in the prior Lumenary audit's next-loop instruction.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:47:- Jack Engler, Being Somebody and Being Nobody, discussed in Psychoanalysis and Buddhism, and practitioner-facing summary at https://mindfulfeeling.ca/on-being-somebody-and-being-nobody/: overlap: Very close for the prerequisite claim. Engler argues that meditation and no-self practice require ego strengths such as self-observation and affect tolerance.; difference: Engler does not split the requirement into five scored load categories or compare Other Power, right effort, Dzogchen, and practice-realization as load distributions.; novelty impact: High reduction. The basic insight that self-dissolving practice needs functional capacities is known.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:55:Unlike Engler, Upaya, Pudgalavada personhood debates, or the prior Lumenary minimum-self claim, this idea says the comparative unit is a five-field load distribution, and that effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization can be tested by where they relocate receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration. Because this follows directly from an earlier Lumenary audit instruction, it is best treated as an extension.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:67:- If: Practice manuals should show patterned safeguards matching their load distribution. Then: Right-effort and gradual-path texts should emphasize intention, repetition, memory, correction, and ethical maintenance. Other-power and direct-introduction texts should not show zero safeguards, but should show safeguards around doubt, false trust, teacher qualification, distraction, antinomian misuse, recognition, and stabilization. Weakens if: Manuals show no relation between path type and safeguard profile, or safeguards track only institution, genre, or teacher personality. Test surface: Coded comparison of SN 45.8, Shinran letters and Tannisho, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho materials, Dogen Bendowa, and contemporary lineage manuals.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:68:- If: Dual-trained practitioners should report different permitted self-capacities when switching methods. Then: The same practitioner reports that vipassana authorizes effortful observation and memory of instructions, Pure Land authorizes relinquishing calculative self-power, Dzogchen authorizes recognition and non-distraction, and Soto practice-realization authorizes full enactment without future-gaining. Weakens if: Reports are explained better by temperament, teacher style, or retreat setting, with no stable method-specific capacity shift. Test surface: Structured interviews with practitioners trained in at least two of Theravada, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Soto Zen, Advaita, and Sufism.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort-f3966ec8d2c9dc68.md:114:- Code primary manuals before using broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho, Shinran letters, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa, and one Advaita prerequisite text.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:16:- Comparison must first preserve the transformation register, such as human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, or causal continuity.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:26:- Dogen, Bendowa, especially sections 3, 4, 7, and 10, https://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/C%20-%20Zen/Ancestors/Dogen/Bendowa/Bendowa.htm
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:28:Structural observation: The Tannisho strongly supports the register-first move. Its decisive register is Other Power, and it names boundary failures such as self-power, calculation, doubt, wrong teacher ownership, and confusing nembutsu with the practitioner's own good act. Bendowa is the anomaly case. It names wrong understanding, false teachers, verbal clinging, and inadequate practice, but its register is practice-realization, where training and enlightenment are not two. The proposed model reads Shinran well, but its interface language strains Dogen because an interface can imply the very separation between practitioner, practice, and realization that Bendowa rejects.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:32:Risk of overread: High. The model may turn ordinary comparative-theology caution into a new technical vocabulary. It may also smuggle in a practitioner-event boundary, even with a self-limitation marker, in traditions where the primary grammar is no-boundary, practice-realization, divine initiative, or nondual enactment.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:38:- Dogen Bendowa practice-realization training and enlightenment are one text
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:56:- Dzogchen pointing-out practitioner sources, example Tergar on pointing out true nature, https://learning.tergar.org/course_library/mingyur-rinpoches-monthly-teachings/mt-august-2019-pointing-out-your-true-nature/: overlap: Close for primordial-awareness interface risks: recognition, misrecognition, teacher mediation, expectation of special experience, and the need to stabilize recognition.; difference: Dzogchen sources provide one register and its risks. The candidate compares that register with Other Power, practice-realization, divine restoration, and effortful paths without reducing them to one agency model.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction. It supports usefulness but not uniqueness.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:60:Unlike Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran, Dogen, and MN 22, this idea claims that comparative work should use a specific two-layer rubric: preserve the transformation register first, then code only tradition-named vulnerabilities, safeguards, and warnings against the rubric itself. Its contribution is operational and predictive, not the discovery that traditions have different registers.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:64:Candidate: Dogen's practice-realization and other no-boundary traditions where decisive transformation is not approached through a separable practitioner-event interface.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:68:Confidence effect: This lowers originality and model confidence. The idea remains useful as a careful comparative heuristic, but it should be classed as extended unless it replaces interface with coding values such as no-boundary, collapsed-boundary, practice-realization, vow-mediated, teacher-mediated, and analyst-frame-refused.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:74:- If: Practice-realization traditions should resist interface grammar more than causal-cultivation or divine-gift traditions. Then: Dogen and Soto materials should correct before-after, means-end, and practitioner-event separations more often than texts framed by gradual effort, vow, grace, or recognition. Weakens if: Practice-realization texts freely use interface-like causal language without corrective pressure, or their corrections are no stronger than in unrelated traditions. Test surface: Bendowa, Genjokoan, selected Shobogenzo fascicles, Soto practice manuals, and teacher interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:81:- Soto Zen teachers familiar with Dogen's practice-realization
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:93:Answers that reduce originality: Practitioners and scholars say this is standard comparative theology, upaya, self-power versus Other Power, practice-realization, apophatic self-limitation, cultural-linguistic theology, or religious coping theory. They also say the rubric does not change teaching decisions or predict student failure modes.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.68 to about 0.56. The register-first discipline is strongly anticipated by comparative theology, hermeneutics, contextualist mysticism scholarship, Lindbeck's cultural-linguistic model, Sharf's critique of generic experience, Pargament's agency styles, Shinran's Other Power, Dogen's practice-realization, and MN 22's self-limiting doctrine use. The remaining contribution is a useful operational extension with predictive fields, not a discovery.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:118:- Replace the single term interface with coded values such as boundary, no-boundary, collapsed-boundary, teacher-mediated, vow-mediated, practice-realization, self-disclosure, and analyst-frame-refused.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:120:- Test primary texts before broad tradition labels: Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, 10, and 11; Shinran letters; Bendowa or Genjokoan; one Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manual; one Christian grace or apophatic source; and one Sufi fana or baqa source.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface-35681329dc02292c.md:123:- Read Freiberger, Clooney, Hedges, Katz, Sharf, Lindbeck, Pargament, Shinran scholarship, Dogen practice-realization scholarship, upaya literature, and apophatic theology before raising novelty above extended.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-register-sensitive-path-interface.md:11:A path should be compared in two ordered layers. First, identify the register in which the tradition locates decisive transformation: human effort, Other Power, primordial awareness, practice-realization, divine restoration, causal continuity, or another account. Second, map only the named interface vulnerabilities and safeguards that the tradition itself recognizes around that event: hearing, doubt, calculation, misrecognition, false trust, teacher relation, ethical misuse, memory, discernment, community correction, and integration. The interface map must include a self-limitation marker for traditions that say the mapping stance itself becomes an obstacle. Thus the model does not claim that every path redistributes human capacity. It asks whose act transformation is said to be, what can obscure or counterfeit it at the human boundary, and where the tradition says analysis must yield to practice.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:18:- Other-power, direct-introduction, effort-centered, and practice-realization paths differ by transfer point, support holder, credited source, forbidden claimant, safeguard, and repair.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:29:Secondary literature gap: The search found close prior structures in religious coping styles, self-power and other-power, Dogen practice-realization, Dzogchen direct introduction, Engler on ego strength before no-self, the Buddhist raft and upaya pattern, and local Lumenary capacity-ledger and credit-distribution work. I did not find the exact field list as a cross-tradition coding sheet, but the core agency-allocation and means-end reversal are well established.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:39:- Dogen practice-realization not means to end shusho
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:50:- Dogen practice-realization, St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen and Stanford Encyclopedia of Philosophy, https://plato.stanford.edu/entries/japanese-zen/: overlap: Close for collapsing practice and realization, removing practice as a bridge to later gain.; difference: Dogen is one type within the proposed rubric, not the whole comparative model.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for the practice-realization category.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:57:Unlike Pargament, self-power and other-power debates, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary credit models, this idea says the decisive unit is a timed transfer for each required function, with observable safeguards and repairs at that transfer point.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:63:Why it strains the model: If even hearing, saying, entrusting, and gratitude are Amida's working rather than trained human functions, then the analyst's transfer language may smuggle self-power into a tradition built to reject that framing. Dogen also strains the model because practice-realization collapses bridge and arrival rather than transferring ownership from one holder to another.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:111:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.53 to about 0.44. The rubric is generative, but its parts are heavily anticipated by religious coping styles, self-power and other-power discourse, Dogen, Dzogchen manuals, the raft and upaya pattern, Engler, and local Lumenary priors. Treat as a consolidation unless inter-rater coding shows new predictive value.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-handoff-point-is-the-variable-2942cf211db9ae34.md:117:- Code primary manuals before broad tradition labels, beginning with SN 45.8, Tannisho chapters 1, 6, 8, and 11, Longchen Rabjam Trekcho, Bendowa or Dogen practice-realization sources, and one Christian grace manual.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:44:- Dogen practice realization one Bendowa Advaita attainment already attained
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:54:- Dogen practice-realization, summarized in St Andrews Encyclopaedia of Theology, https://www.saet.ac.uk/Buddhism/Dogen: overlap: Close for activity-centered credit. Dogen's praxis is enlightenment, so practice is not merely a cause toward a later result.; difference: Dogen provides one type, not a comparative credit-distribution taxonomy.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction for one category.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:113:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.74 to about 0.48. The five-type comparative frame is generative, but the main structure is anticipated by Pargament's religious coping styles, God-control attribution research, Christian monergism and synergism, Japanese self-power and other-power, Sri Vaishnava prapatti debates, Sufi station-state distinctions, Dogen practice-realization, and local Lumenary work.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-whose-doing-is-this-credit-distribution-as-a-practice-variable-5e22b929e230f390.md:120:- Treat activity-centered and ground-centered categories as the only possible novelty zones, and search Dogen, Advaita, Dzogchen, and nondual scholarship for close prior forms.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:31:Secondary literature gap: The audit searched conversion studies, doctrine-as-grammar theory, religious coping agency styles, sociology of plausibility structures, liminality, situated learning, upaya, Shinran Other Power, Orange grace canons, Dogen practice-realization, religious socialization, and prior Lumenary capacity-ledger audits. It did not fully close-read Augustine against Pelagius, Longchenpa or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals, Sufi bayah and fana texts, Sri Vaishnava prapatti sources, or original-language terms for faith, entrusting, effort, capacity, grace, and agency. That gap blocks a candidate-discovery claim.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:43:- Dogen Bendowa practice realization are one translation
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:59:- Soto Zen teaching on practice and realization, https://www.sotozen.com/eng/library/stories/vol01.html: overlap: Close for practice-realization, where practice is not merely a beginner's method leading later to realization but is already implicated in realization.; difference: The candidate's first-break and claimant categories may not map cleanly onto Dogen-style practice-realization because beginning and fulfillment are deliberately collapsed.; novelty impact: Moderate reduction and strong anomaly pressure. Dogen-style cases may force values such as no-transfer, practice-realization, or analyst-frame-refused.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:69:Candidate: Inherited practice and Dogen-style practice-realization cases, especially cradle religious formation and Soto Zen's refusal to separate practice from realization.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:71:Why it strains the model: Inherited formation may have no discrete first-break moment, and practice-realization may refuse the sequence of entry, support transfer, claimant prohibition, safeguard, and later verification. In these cases, the model's entry grammar may be an analyst artifact rather than a native structure.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:73:Confidence effect: Lowers confidence from candidate-discovery range to extended or renamed range until the rubric includes no-threshold, gradual-socialization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values, then survives blind coding.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:77:- If: Entry doctrine and claimant prohibition are separable variables in at least some traditions. Then: Blind coders using only entry texts can distinguish entry mechanism from forbidden claimant, and those separate codes predict different warning and verification patterns in later manuals with above-chance agreement. Weakens if: Coders cannot separate entry mechanism from claimant rule, or later safeguards can be predicted equally well from generic tradition labels, conversion-stage theory, religious socialization, or Pargament agency styles. Test surface: Split-source manual coding across Shinran Pure Land, Theravada path-factor texts, Orange or Augustinian grace texts, Dogen practice-realization, and Dzogchen or Mahamudra pointing-out manuals.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-entry-claimant-grammar-756dc4935ec9d174.md:79:- If: Hybrid or cross-training friction should often occur at claimant boundaries, not only at doctrine or technique boundaries. Then: Practitioners moving between effort-centered, grace-centered, teacher-recognition-centered, and practice-realization paths report confusion about who or what is allowed to own progress, failure, verification, or decisive transformation. Weakens if: Reported friction clusters around vocabulary, social identity, ritual preference, or teacher relationship without identifiable claimant-boundary conflicts. Test surface: Structured interviews with dual-trained practitioners and teachers, coded independently from doctrinal affiliation.
