./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation-fd9108753ae68e6a.md:79:- If: Dissolution target and residue policy exert independent pressure on continuity placement. Then: Coders who see only doctrinal negation passages can predict above baseline whether later manuals locate support in effort, attention, teacher, vow, grace, ritual, community, text, or no-boundary practice-realization. Weakens if: Prediction fails, or ritual form, institution type, teacher authority, socialization pattern, or historical borrowing predicts support placement better than dissolution target and residue policy. Test surface: Split-source blind coding across Theravada, Advaita, Soto Zen, Jodo Shinshu, Dzogchen or Mahamudra, Christian grace, Sufi fana and baqa, and secular mindfulness manuals.
