./runs/20260526-110005-codex-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:23:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md:1:# Dogen's Shobogenzo: "Uji" (Being-Time)
./notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md:7:Attribution: Eihei Dogen (1200-1253), written 1240
./notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md:21:**Uji and Block Universe (Physics):** Dogen's dharma-positions (each moment complete, not flowing into the next) parallel the B-theory of time and the block universe. Vorenkamp argues Dogen contains "all the main elements of McTaggart's B-series." But Dogen is not simply an eternalist; nikon gives each moment experiential primacy, closer to "block universe plus experiential indexicality."
./notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md:25:**Dogen and the Lankavatara:** The Lankavatara's "all things are nothing but what is seen of the mind" provides the ground for Dogen's claim that each moment of being-time contains all of existence. If no reality exists "outside" mind, each moment of conscious being IS the totality.
./notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md:27:**Firewood-Ash and the Inferential Gap:** Dogen's refusal to see firewood "becoming" ash; each abides in its own dharma-position; is a temporal version of the inferential gap. What do you infer from the observation that firewood is followed by ash? Causation? Transformation? Dogen says: neither. Each is complete.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:51:- Is this already obvious as two truths, healthy ego before no-self, practice-realization, surrender, or grace?
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:234:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:247:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:375:When a practice removes the ordinary self, the sharpest cross-tradition difference may be the grammar each system allows after negation. Advaita lets the remainder speak like a noun, the unobjectifiable knower. Early Buddhism treats the candidate self as a predicate failure across the aggregates. Madhyamaka turns the remainder into a self-canceling rule against fixed views. Daoism makes it an adverbial manner, action without forcing. Dogen makes it a tense, the complete present act. Ibn Arabi makes it an address, the world as divine disclosure. The comparison unit is not only what remains, but what grammatical role the remainder is permitted to play.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1202:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1258:The familiar near-neighbor is Engler's claim that a person needs enough ego strength for self-observation and affect tolerance before no-self practice. The exact difference is that this model does not ask whether a healthy self is required in general. It splits the requirement into five capacities and tracks where each capacity is placed across stages of the path. Pudgalavada debates, Collins on selfless persons, Buddhist functional-self accounts, and contemporary self-pattern theory already make the Buddhist continuity problem hard to ignore. The exact difference is cross-tradition and architectural: the model predicts that effortful, other-power, direct-introduction, and practice-realization traditions will distribute receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration differently. The closest new pressure comes from Pure Land and Dzogchen. Instead of treating them as anomalies that need no self-capacity, the model predicts that they compress the capacity load into hearing, entrusting, recognition, teacher relation, and post-recognition stabilization. That graded relocation is the potentially original contribution, while the basic insight that self-dissolving practice needs functional capacities is strongly precedented.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1267:- Dogen practice-realization materials in notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md and prior local observations. Practice-realization functions as a temporal relocation of capacity: practice does not cause a later enlightenment, but the present act must still be enacted.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1455:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1515:- Primary close-reading: Dogen, Bendowa, Kazuaki Tanahashi translation, https://www.lionsroar.com/just-wholeheartedly-sit/. Dogen says the dharma is abundant in each person yet not actualized without practice, and that practice and realization cannot be recognized as two separate things. This makes the present act a support locus while forbidding future-gaining ownership.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1517:- Near-neighbor search: Jack Engler, You Must Be Somebody Before You Can Be Nobody, https://inquiringmind.com/article/0501_1_engler-interview/; Bhikkhu Analayo, Skill in Means and Mindfulness, https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s12671-021-01795-2; Harvard Divinity Bulletin on Buddhist skillful means, https://bulletin.hds.harvard.edu/buddhist-studies-the-buddhist-way/. These sources cover ego strength, capacity-sensitive teaching, and pedagogical adaptation, but not a two-part code of support locus plus forbidden claimant across effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1552:- If this model is right, then adverse contemplative events should cluster around wrong-claimant failures: self-power anxiety in gift practice, achievement seeking in practice-realization, reification after direct introduction, and mechanical striving in effort practice. If adverse reports do not vary by claimant pattern after controlling for trauma, intensity, and supervision, the model is weakened.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1637:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1648:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
./runs/20260526-150002-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1798:- Test the rubric on Abhidharma and Heart Sutra, Advaita identity and negation, Sufi longing and return, Daoist decrease, and Zen practice-realization.
