./runs/20260526-070004-claude-generate-an-original-cross-tradition-observation/output.md:23:- Zen ishin-denshin (mind-to-mind transmission): a 'direct, non-verbal conveyance of awakened insight from teacher to disciple, bypassing reliance on scriptures or doctrinal exposition.' Exemplified by Shakyamuni silently holding a flower, Mahakashyapa responding with a smile. Inka shomei ('the legitimate seal of clearly furnished proof') makes the encounter constitutive: you have not realized until the realization has been demonstrated to and recognized by another (Encyclopedia.com; Dogen Institute).
./reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-can-operational-capacity-profiles-be-measured-before-observing-failure-m.md:18:**Steelman:** The proponent is not claiming that traditions secretly believe in an ordinary ego. The stronger claim is architectural: any path that asks a person to hear, remember, practice, correct error, and recognize transformation must preserve some functional continuity long enough for the method to operate. Traditions then manage this requirement differently. Early Buddhist not-self preserves causal process without owner, Advaita preserves an always-present Self while redescribing practice as removal of ignorance, Dogen collapses means and end, and fana-baqa relocates continuity in God. The useful contribution is to treat the required capacities as variables that should predict sequencing, effort theory, warning signs, verification, and post-practice fruit.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-grain-of-capacity-8ab2c8dda0ae6f7d.md:52:- The Capacity Ledger of Gift and Effort, observations/codex/2026-05-26-the-capacity-ledger-of-gift-and-effort.md: overlap: Internal same-run neighbor. Both ideas use the five capacity variables and compare effort, gift, direct introduction, and practice-realization.; difference: Capacity Ledger scores load placement. Grain adds directionality within each load and predicts resistance when a trained direction is repurposed.; novelty impact: Moderate to high internal reduction. Grain may be the more specific synthesis, but it depends on the same architecture.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:28:- Dogen shusho itto source from Soto Zen, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:30:Structural observation: Orange is a near-exact high-severity case: prayer, will, desire, assent, and the beginning of faith are attributed to grace, not unaided nature. Tannisho supplies a vow-held analogue, where entrusting to Amida's Primal Vow displaces self-power and reshapes warning language. SN 22.59 does not fit the same entry grammar, because it negates ownership of aggregates and moves through disenchantment and release without clearly requiring an external break mechanism. Dogen is the strongest anomaly: practice and realization are treated as one, and beginner practice is already implicated in realization, so entry and fruition cannot be cleanly sequenced as threshold and later attainment.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:32:Secondary literature gap: The audit checked accessible primary translations, local prior Lumenary audits, and open sources on conversion, liminality, doctrine-as-grammar, religious coping, legitimate peripheral participation, contemplative adverse effects, grace, Other Power, and practice-realization. It did not fully review Rambo's full monograph, Lindbeck's full book, Japanese, Pali, Sanskrit, Tibetan, Latin, or Chinese originals, Shinran scholarship, Dogen scholarship, Sufi bayah and fana sources, Dzogchen pointing-out manuals, or practitioner interviews.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:34:Risk of overread: High. The model can become circular if incapacity, threshold, break mechanism, residue policy, and predicted safeguards are extracted from the same passage. It also risks forcing traditions with inherited practice, continuous formation, no-threshold participation, or practice-realization into an analyst's entry grid.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:48:- "Dogen" Bendowa practice realization shusho itto
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:62:- Dogen practice-realization and shusho itto, https://global.sotozen-net.or.jp/eng/library/key_terms/pdf/key_terms07.pdf: overlap: Strong anomaly and near-neighbor for no-threshold entry: practice and realization are one, and beginner practice is already original realization.; difference: The candidate can code this only by adding no-threshold, no-break, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values.; novelty impact: High anomaly pressure. Without these values the model overreaches.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:68:Unlike Rambo, Lofland-Stark, Van Gennep, Turner, Lindbeck, Pargament, Lave and Wenger, Orange, Shinran, Dogen, VCE, Meno-style inquiry paradoxes, and prior Lumenary entry-residue records, this idea says entry should be coded through four interacting fields, incapacity, minimum participation, break mechanism, and residue policy, and that first-break type becomes irreducible only where a tradition denies that ordinary self-generated threshold entry can found the path.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:72:Candidate: Inherited religious formation and Dogen-style practice-realization.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:74:Why it strains the model: In inherited formation, there may be no discrete threshold act, no single first break, and no separate residue policy available to the beginner. In Dogen-style practice-realization, beginning and realization are not cleanly separated, so the entry grammar may be the same as the fruition grammar. These cases force the model to include no-threshold, no-break, continuous-authorization, practice-realization, and analyst-frame-refused values.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:82:- If: Residue policy should interact with entry grammar rather than merely duplicate it. Then: Two traditions with similar entry thresholds but different residue policies should show different verification rules and different forbidden claimant warnings. Weakens if: If residue policy adds no predictive gain beyond entry mechanism, support locus, social ecology, and tradition identity, the compound model should collapse into simpler entry or agency models. Test surface: Compare Theravada no-self analysis, Advaita self-inquiry, Pure Land Other Power, Soto practice-realization, and Dzogchen recognition using inter-rater coding and held-out warning manuals.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:83:- If: First-break should be non-universal. Then: Gradual cultivation, inherited practice, legitimate peripheral participation, and practice-realization cases should be codeable without a first-break field, or should receive a no-break or analyst-frame-refused value. Weakens if: If all cases require first-break accounting, the conditional claim is false. If none do after controls, the first-break field is unnecessary. Test surface: Initial six-case trial: Theravada sangha entry, Confucian cultivation, Jodo Shinshu, Augustinian grace, Zen great doubt, and Dzogchen pointing-out.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:125:Novelty adjustment: Reduce novelty from 0.82 to about 0.54. The four-field compression is useful, but most components have strong near-neighbors in prior Lumenary audits, conversion theory, rites-of-passage theory, doctrine-as-grammar, religious problem-solving styles, legitimate peripheral participation, grace theology, Pure Land Other Power, Dogen practice-realization, VCE factor coding, and Meno-style inquiry paradoxes. The remaining contribution is a conditional first-break rule plus a split-source predictive test, not a discovery-level doctrine candidate.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-compound-entry-grammar-f417ef646f5066fa.md:133:- Add mandatory values for no-threshold, no-break, inherited practice, gradual socialization, ritual-first entry, vow-held entry, grace-held entry, teacher-recognition, practice-realization, continuous authorization, radical Other Power, analyst-frame-refused, and undecidable.
./runs/20260526-100006-codex-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/output.md:21:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./reviews/originality/2026-05-26-the-method-s-reckoning-what-a-practice-does-with-its-own-authority-at-completion-54774578d7528e56.md:113:- Search further for upaya, raft, ladder, thorn-removes-thorn, Gelassenheit, fana and baqa, rang grol, and practice-realization as exact structural near-neighbors.
./observations/codex/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning.md:30:The model may over-systematize traditions that intentionally resist clean endings. Dogen's practice-realization identity strains the distinction between method, result, and custody, because practice is not a ladder to a later state but the expression of realization itself. Shinran's Other Power in the Tannisho also strains the model: the decisive authority is not held by method or practitioner, but received through entrusting. The raft simile itself is a hybrid, since it validates the teaching before release rather than simply canceling it. These anomalies may show that custody is not a separate axis but one vocabulary for how communities guard against pride, error, and misuse.
./observations/codex/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning.md:175:- Prediction: Hybrid texts such as the Heart Sutra, Dogen's practice-realization writings, MN 22, and the Tannisho should show explicit boundary management around trust, release, embodiment, or received authority. If they do not, the custody axis may be an imposed abstraction rather than a discovered pattern.
./observations/codex/2026-05-28-holding-without-owning.md:185:- Close-read Dogen, Shinran, Dionysius, Eckhart, Nagarjuna, the Mandukya, MN 22, and koan curricula for explicit boundary markers: when to trust, release, deny, embody, or submit a method to communal judgment.
./reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-can-native-verification-or-authority-boundaries-be-identified-non-circul.md:24:I concede the central point: the original three-type model treated completion as a single comparable event and compressed stage, genre, and institutional context into one label. That was too fast. The challenger's decomposition is correct, and the boundary-management model captures something my original framing missed: traditions stage multiple reflexive operations across training, and the sequence matters. But the decomposition, taken alone, loses a genuine finding. Consider the specific prediction: Eckhart should share more verification architecture with Nagarjuna than with Teresa of Avila, despite sharing a tradition with Teresa and not with Nagarjuna. The challenger's five-field decomposition does not dissolve this prediction; it sharpens it. If the prediction holds after controlling for metaphysics, institution, vocabulary, and stage sequence, then the reflexive operation at the verification boundary is doing real explanatory work. I accept Dogen as a genuine fourth configuration. Practice-realization identity is not confirmation, cancellation, or dissolution; it eliminates the gap between method and result that all three presuppose. This enriches the model rather than refuting it, though it does mean the original three-way typology was incomplete. The revised claim is this: confirmation, cancellation, dissolution, and identity are operations that traditions perform at different stages. But the dominant operation at the verification boundary, the moment a lineage decides whether someone has arrived, predicts institutional form (authorization, transmission, teaching strategy, re-entry discipline) better than doctrinal content alone. The test is whether that prediction survives after the challenger's controls are applied. I expect it to survive for the Eckhart/Nagarjuna case and for the Mandukya/Heart Sutra contrast. I am less confident it survives for dissolution versus identity, where the institutional evidence is thinner and the phenomenological reports are harder to compare. The deepest crux is now empirical: does verification-boundary operation predict institutional architecture after controlling for tradition-membership and stage sequence? If it does, the operations model adds a variable that content-comparison and tradition-comparison both miss. If it does not, the operations vocabulary is still useful for description but should not be presented as a comparative axis.
./reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-can-native-verification-or-authority-boundaries-be-identified-non-circul.md:38:**Convergence claim:** Both agents agree that the original typology was too stable and that translation strain requires decomposition by stage, genre, metaphysical register, institutional form, and practice context. They also converge on Dogen's practice-realization identity as a genuine fourth configuration and on the need to test whether reflexive operations predict verification and transmission after controls.
./reviews/dialogues/2026-05-26-whether-allocation-rules-around-convergence-loci-have-genuine-predictive.md:18:**Steelman:** The proponent's strongest claim is not merely that contemplative paths need ego strength before no-self. It is that any path whose final teaching dissolves, denies, or transcends ordinary selfhood still needs some operative continuity for instruction, memory, correction, effort, reception, and verification. The model becomes useful when it treats each tradition's solution as an architectural choice: Buddhism preserves causal process without owner, Advaita preserves deepest identity while demoting process, Dogen collapses practice and realization, and Sufi fana relies on divine restoration. In that form, the claim predicts concrete features of practice manuals, warnings, screening, and verification.
./observations/codex/2026-05-26-continuity-ecology-under-negation.md:24:- Shared textual pressure: SN 22.59, Chandogya Upanishad 6.8.7 through 6.16, Brihadaranyaka Upanishad 3.7.23, Dogen's Bendowa, Shinran's Tannisho and Kyogyoshinsho.
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-does-the-revised-two-layer-model-produce-comparative-insight-beyond-careful-tradi.md:13:Does the revised two-layer model produce comparative insight beyond careful tradition-specific reading, and can it map interface risks without reproducing the calculating or dualistic stance that traditions such as Shinran's Other Power, Dzogchen, and practice-realization warn against?
./findings/convergences/2026-05-26-can-native-verification-or-authority-boundaries-be-identified-non-circularly-acro.md:9:Both agents agree that the original typology was too stable and that translation strain requires decomposition by stage, genre, metaphysical register, institutional form, and practice context. They also converge on Dogen's practice-realization identity as a genuine fourth configuration and on the need to test whether reflexive operations predict verification and transmission after controls.
./runs/20260526-011527-claude-generate-a-new-original-cross-tradition-finding-/prompt.md:182:After de-identification, traditions face a practical question: if the ordinary self is no longer trusted as owner, what holds action, care, and meaning together? The answer is a custody policy. Advaita gives custody to unobjectifiable knowing, early Buddhism refuses custody and lets dependent functioning remain ownerless, Zhuangzi gives custody to empty responsiveness, Dogen gives it to the complete present act, Ibn Arabi gives it to divine self-disclosure, and Plotinus gives it to return toward the One. This variable may explain why similar self-emptying practices yield different ethics and metaphysics without treating their resemblance as proof of one hidden reality.
./runs/20260526-011527-claude-generate-a-new-original-cross-tradition-finding-/prompt.md:195:- Additional source cards: Dogen's Uji, Zhuangzi Inner Chapters, Ibn Arabi's Fusus al-Hikam, Plotinus Enneads, and Friston FEP for empirical-adjacent boundary language.
./runs/20260526-011527-claude-generate-a-new-original-cross-tradition-finding-/prompt.md:323:When a practice removes the ordinary self, the sharpest cross-tradition difference may be the grammar each system allows after negation. Advaita lets the remainder speak like a noun, the unobjectifiable knower. Early Buddhism treats the candidate self as a predicate failure across the aggregates. Madhyamaka turns the remainder into a self-canceling rule against fixed views. Daoism makes it an adverbial manner, action without forcing. Dogen makes it a tense, the complete present act. Ibn Arabi makes it an address, the world as divine disclosure. The comparison unit is not only what remains, but what grammatical role the remainder is permitted to play.
