./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1202:- Dogen, Bendowa practice-verification unity, summarized at Encyclopedia of Buddhism, https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen. Used as a countercase where distance is treated as a mistaken split inside practice.
./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1258:The familiar near-neighbor is Engler's claim that a person needs enough ego strength for self-observation and affect tolerance before no-self practice. The exact difference is that this model does not ask whether a healthy self is required in general. It splits the requirement into five capacities and tracks where each capacity is placed across stages of the path. Pudgalavada debates, Collins on selfless persons, Buddhist functional-self accounts, and contemporary self-pattern theory already make the Buddhist continuity problem hard to ignore. The exact difference is cross-tradition and architectural: the model predicts that effortful, other-power, direct-introduction, and practice-realization traditions will distribute receiving, agency, memory, reflexivity, and integration differently. The closest new pressure comes from Pure Land and Dzogchen. Instead of treating them as anomalies that need no self-capacity, the model predicts that they compress the capacity load into hearing, entrusting, recognition, teacher relation, and post-recognition stabilization. That graded relocation is the potentially original contribution, while the basic insight that self-dissolving practice needs functional capacities is strongly precedented.
./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1267:- Dogen practice-realization materials in notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md and prior local observations. Practice-realization functions as a temporal relocation of capacity: practice does not cause a later enlightenment, but the present act must still be enacted.
./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1455:- Dogen, Bendowa and source card notes/source-cards/buddhism-dogen-uji.md, for practice-realization and present-tense enactment as a check on goal-seeking effort.
./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1574:- Thinking method source: Dogen, Bendowa, practice and verification as one, summarized in Encyclopedia of Buddhism: https://www.encyclopediaofbuddhism.org/wiki/Dogen
./runs/20260526-143005-claude-generate-original-cross-tradition-observations-c/prompt.md:1585:The model can romanticize distance and make real suffering, ignorance, or alienation look useful. A Buddhist gradual path may say distance is not a noble instrument but a condition to end through training. A Zen enactment path may say treating no-distance as a function already misses practice-realization. A Sufi may say longing is not a psychological tool but the trace of a real Beloved. The Dogen lens used here may bias the comparison against causal paths by making sequence look like delusion; the mindfulness lens may over-neutralize devotion by turning longing into an observed state. The idea should be weakened unless close practice texts show that each path deliberately trains with its distance policy.
